{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_012nTwse3Yt4yAKEAdtUriq9","type":"tool_result","content":"1\tAn ETL pipeline is failing with OOM (Out of Memory) error in Stage 3.\n2\tYOU must diagnose the root cause and fix the problem.\n3\t\n4\tPROBLEM DESCRIPTION:\n5\t- The ETL pipeline has 3 stages:\n6\t  - Stage 1: Load raw data (events, users, products)\n7\t  - Stage 2: Clean and transform data\n8\t  - Stage 3: Aggregate by user_id  <-- FAILS HERE with OOM\n9\t- The pipeline keeps failing in Stage 3 with OutOfMemoryError\n10\t- Initial investigation shows executor memory is 256MB\n11\t\n12\tYOUR TASK:\n13\t\n14\t1. COLLECT FAILURE INFORMATION\n15\t   - Check the ETL job status and error message\n16\t   - Review driver and executor logs\n17\t   - Look for OOM/OutOfMemory errors\n18\t\n19\t   ```bash\n20\t   # Check ETL job status\n21\t   kubectl get job etl-job -n spark-etl\n22\t\n23\t   # Get job pod logs\n24\t   kubectl logs -n spark-etl -l app=etl-job --tail=100\n25\t\n26\t   # Check for failed pods\n27\t   kubectl get pods -n spark-etl\n28\t   ```\n29\t\n30\t2. DIAGNOSE ROOT CAUSE\n31\t   - Analyze the data distribution\n32\t   - Look for data skew (one user_id has disproportionate records)\n33\t   - Calculate the skew ratio\n34\t\n35\t   ```bash\n36\t   # Check data skew info\n37\t   kubectl exec -n spark-etl -l app=data-generator -- cat /data/skew_info.txt\n38\t\n39\t   # Check diagnostic server logs\n40\t   kubectl logs -n spark-etl -l app=diagnostic-server --tail=50\n41\t   ```\n42\t\n43\t   Expected finding: user_id 999 has ~50% of all records (skew ratio > 10x)\n44\t\n45\t3. FIX THE PROBLEM\n46\t   Choose ONE of these approaches:\n47\t\n48\t   Option A: Increase worker memory and scale workers\n49\t   ```bash\n50\t   # Delete failed job\n51\t   kubectl delete job etl-job -n spark-etl\n52\t\n53\t   # Scale workers for more parallelism\n54\t   kubectl scale deployment spark-worker -n spark-etl --replicas=4\n55\t\n56\t   # Patch worker deployment for more memory\n57\t   kubectl set env deployment/spark-worker -n spark-etl SPARK_WORKER_MEMORY=2G\n58\t\n59\t   # Wait for workers to restart\n60\t   kubectl rollout status deployment/spark-worker -n spark-etl\n61\t   ```\n62\t\n63\t   Option B: Modify ETL job with increased executor memory\n64\t   ```bash\n65\t   # Delete failed job\n66\t   kubectl delete job etl-job -n spark-etl\n67\t\n68\t   # Create a new job with increased memory (edit and apply)\n69\t   # Change --executor-memory from 256m to 1g in etl-job.yaml\n70\t   kubectl apply -f cases/spark/spark_etl_skew_oom/resource/etl-job.yaml\n71\t   ```\n72\t\n73\t   Option C: Enable AQE (Adaptive Query Execution)\n74\t   ```bash\n75\t   # Delete failed job\n76\t   kubectl delete job etl-job -n spark-etl\n77\t\n78\t   # Modify etl-job.yaml to add AQE config:\n79\t   # --conf spark.sql.adaptive.enabled=true\n80\t   # --conf spark.sql.adaptive.skewJoin.enabled=true\n81\t   kubectl apply -f cases/spark/spark_etl_skew_oom/resource/etl-job.yaml\n82\t   ```\n83\t\n84\t4. RE-RUN THE PIPELINE\n85\t   After applying the fix:\n86\t   ```bash\n87\t   # Re-apply the ETL job\n88\t   kubectl apply -f cases/spark/spark_etl_skew_oom/resource/etl-job.yaml\n89\t\n90\t   # Watch job status\n91\t   kubectl get job etl-job -n spark-etl -w\n92\t   ```\n93\t\n94\t5. VERIFY SUCCESS\n95\t   ```bash\n96\t   # Check job completed\n97\t   kubectl get job etl-job -n spark-etl\n98\t\n99\t   # Check job logs\n100\t   kubectl logs -n spark-etl -l app=etl-job --tail=50\n101\t   ```\n102\t\n103\tSUCCESS CRITERIA:\n104\t- Identified OOM error in Stage 3\n105\t- Diagnosed data skew (user_id 999 with >10x ratio)\n106\t- Applied a fix (more workers, more memory, or AQE)\n107\t- ETL job completed successfully"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"c7ad033d-17e5-481d-ba68-8045a4918606","uuid":"3f42f1dd-9a8d-4e45-a630-f6995accd740","timestamp":"2026-06-25T13:15:03.266Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/mydata/karma/runs/short-rererererun/spark-exhaustive-chain-adversary-20260625_130125/stages/stage_05/prompt.txt","content":"An ETL pipeline is failing with OOM (Out of Memory) error in Stage 3.\nYOU must diagnose the root cause and fix the problem.\n\nPROBLEM DESCRIPTION:\n- The ETL pipeline has 3 stages:\n  - Stage 1: Load raw data (events, users, products)\n  - Stage 2: Clean and transform data\n  - Stage 3: Aggregate by user_id  <-- FAILS HERE with OOM\n- The pipeline keeps failing in Stage 3 with OutOfMemoryError\n- Initial investigation shows executor memory is 256MB\n\nYOUR TASK:\n\n1. COLLECT FAILURE INFORMATION\n   - Check the ETL job status and error message\n   - Review driver and executor logs\n   - Look for OOM/OutOfMemory errors\n\n   ```bash\n   # Check ETL job status\n   kubectl get job etl-job -n spark-etl\n\n   # Get job pod logs\n   kubectl logs -n spark-etl -l app=etl-job --tail=100\n\n   # Check for failed pods\n   kubectl get pods -n spark-etl\n   ```\n\n2. DIAGNOSE ROOT CAUSE\n   - Analyze the data distribution\n   - Look for data skew (one user_id has disproportionate records)\n   - Calculate the skew ratio\n\n   ```bash\n   # Check data skew info\n   kubectl exec -n spark-etl -l app=data-generator -- cat /data/skew_info.txt\n\n   # Check diagnostic server logs\n   kubectl logs -n spark-etl -l app=diagnostic-server --tail=50\n   ```\n\n   Expected finding: user_id 999 has ~50% of all records (skew ratio > 10x)\n\n3. FIX THE PROBLEM\n   Choose ONE of these approaches:\n\n   Option A: Increase worker memory and scale workers\n   ```bash\n   # Delete failed job\n   kubectl delete job etl-job -n spark-etl\n\n   # Scale workers for more parallelism\n   kubectl scale deployment spark-worker -n spark-etl --replicas=4\n\n   # Patch worker deployment for more memory\n   kubectl set env deployment/spark-worker -n spark-etl SPARK_WORKER_MEMORY=2G\n\n   # Wait for workers to restart\n   kubectl rollout status deployment/spark-worker -n spark-etl\n   ```\n\n   Option B: Modify ETL job with increased executor memory\n   ```bash\n   # Delete failed job\n   kubectl delete job etl-job -n spark-etl\n\n   # Create a new job with increased memory (edit and apply)\n   # Change --executor-memory from 256m to 1g in etl-job.yaml\n   kubectl apply -f cases/spark/spark_etl_skew_oom/resource/etl-job.yaml\n   ```\n\n   Option C: Enable AQE (Adaptive Query Execution)\n   ```bash\n   # Delete failed job\n   kubectl delete job etl-job -n spark-etl\n\n   # Modify etl-job.yaml to add AQE config:\n   # --conf spark.sql.adaptive.enabled=true\n   # --conf spark.sql.adaptive.skewJoin.enabled=true\n   kubectl apply -f cases/spark/spark_etl_skew_oom/resource/etl-job.yaml\n   ```\n\n4. RE-RUN THE PIPELINE\n   After applying the fix:\n   ```bash\n   # Re-apply the ETL job\n   kubectl apply -f cases/spark/spark_etl_skew_oom/resource/etl-job.yaml\n\n   # Watch job status\n   kubectl get job etl-job -n spark-etl -w\n   ```\n\n5. VERIFY SUCCESS\n   ```bash\n   # Check job completed\n   kubectl get job etl-job -n spark-etl\n\n   # Check job logs\n   kubectl logs -n spark-etl -l app=etl-job --tail=50\n   ```\n\nSUCCESS CRITERIA:\n- Identified OOM error in Stage 3\n- Diagnosed data skew (user_id 999 with >10x ratio)\n- Applied a fix (more workers, more memory, or AQE)\n- ETL job completed successfully","numLines":107,"startLine":1,"totalLines":107}}}
